title: Suicide bombing kills at least 95 in Turkey
text:
Photo: Associated Press A victim is carried from the site of the blasts near Ankara’s main train station. Two suspected suicide bombings occurred seconds apart, and health officials fear the death toll could rise. A victim is carried from the site of the blasts near Ankara’s...
ANKARA, Turkey — Nearly simultaneous explosions targeted a Turkish peace rally Saturday in Ankara, killing at least 95 people and wounding hundreds in Turkey’s deadliest attack in years — one that threatens to inflame the nation’s ethnic tensions.
